                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18151025-56-off319 t18151025-56-crimeloc322"></join> On the 23rd of September, between eleven and twelve o'clock, I was standing at my bar, I saw the prisoner at the bar, coming down the stairs, with several articles of wearing apparel, belonging to my family, in his possession. I asked him what he had in that bundle; he said, they were his own clothes. Then I went gently round the bar, and laid hold of the bundle,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181510250023"></xptr>and found it contained the articles named in the indictment, which are my property.</p>
